# HomeVault environment
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values, then restart the dev server
# (Expo reads .env at startup, not per-reload):
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Both values come from the Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#
# The EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix is required for Expo to expose a variable to app code.
# It also means these are **inlined into the JS bundle at build time** — they are
# configuration, not secrets, and anyone can read them out of the shipped app.
# That is fine for the two below and true of nothing else:
#
#   - the publishable key is designed to be public. On its own it grants no data
#     access at all, because every table's RLS policy requires a signed-in user
#     (see database/schema.sql).
#   - the service_role key must NEVER appear here or in any EXPO_PUBLIC_ var. It
#     bypasses RLS entirely. It belongs only to the Edge Function, where Supabase
#     injects it server-side (see supabase/README.md).

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-PUBLISHABLE-KEY
